video:video.video:description: Here's the latest for Wednesday, Feb. 11th: Bondi comes under fire from Congress; Trump tells Netanyahu that negotiations with Iran continue;FBI in search for clues in Nancy Guthrie's disappearance; El Paso airspace closure tied to Mexican cartel drones.

video:video.video:title: Bondi clashes with Democrats in 5-hour hearing as she struggles to turn the page on Epstein files furor
video:video.video:description: Attorney General Pam Bondi launched into a passionate defense of President Donald Trump, repeatedly shouting at Democrats during a combative hearing.

video:video.video:title: AP reporter attends Milan's daily pin hunt that has Olympic collectors running to landmarks
video:video.video:description: Olympic pin collectors in Milan turn each morning into a sprint for a small prize. On Wednesday, fans gather before 8 a.m. and then race to a landmark after YesMilano posts the day’s lineup spot online.

video:video.video:title: Lawyer for woman who survived ICE shooting says, 'we cannot trust our federal government'
video:video.video:description: Investigative materials made public Tuesday showed that after shooting Marimar Martínez five times in October, Border Patrol Agent Charles Exum joked about it in a text chat with colleagues and was praised by them and boss Border Patrol Cmdr.

video:video.video:title: Analysis as Europe warily readies for Munich Security Conference amid troubled trans-Atlantic ties
video:video.video:description: European leaders are heading into this year’s Munich Security Conference amid deep unease about the state of the trans-Atlantic alliance.

video:video.video:title: US energy secretary meets Venezuela's acting president to assess oil industry overhaul
video:video.video:description: United States Energy Secretary Chris Wright arrived Wednesday in Venezuela for a firsthand assessment of the country's oil industry, a visit that further asserts the U.S. government's self-appointed role in turning around Venezuela’s dilapidated energy sector.

video:video.video:title: San Francisco teachers strike leaves 50,000 students out of school
video:video.video:description: The San Francisco Unified School District’s 120 schools remained closed for a third day Wednesday, after about 6,000 public schoolteachers went on strike over higher wages, health benefits and more resources for students with special needs.

video:video.video:title: Polls open for Bangladesh’s first election since 2024 uprising that ousted former PM Hasina
video:video.video:description: Polls opened across Bangladesh on Thursday for voters to cast ballots in a parliamentary election seen as a critical test of the country’s democracy after years of political turmoil.

video:video.video:title: FBI combs desert terrain for clues in Nancy Guthrie's disappearance
video:video.video:description: FBI agents walked among rocks and desert vegetation at Nancy Guthrie's Tucson-area home on Wednesday searching for clues in her disappearance.

video:video.video:title: Annie Guthrie's neighbor reveals FBI questions in search for Nancy
video:video.video:description: A neighbor of a daughter of missing woman Nancy Guthrie revealed on Wednesday what FBI agents asked her during a search in an area of Arizona. (AP video by Ty O'Neil)

video:video.video:title: Kosovo's political deadlock ends as new parliament approves Kurti government
video:video.video:description: Kosovo's new parliament on Wednesday swiftly approved a new government of Prime Minister Albin Kurti, ending more than a yearlong political deadlock in the Balkan country.

video:video.video:title: Portugal PM urges residents to leave homes as partial collapse of dike set to exacerbate flooding crisis
video:video.video:description: Portugal’s prime minister urged residents in flood-hit areas to leave their homes after a dike partly collapsed in the central region of Coimbra.
